race.comment: This race has been knocked about by scratchings with a couple of the leading fancies coming out. That now leaves BRUTAL ELEGANCE (5) as the main player. She hit the line well for second at Bathurst and should appreciate the extra ground. Drawn to get every chance. MY CROWN (3) led and dominated over 1200m at Bathurst. Jumps sharply in distance but can give another bold sight. CASINO DIVA (6) strips fitter fourth-up and put the writing on the wall with an improved effort for fourth last time out. Can figure with a smart ride from the awkward alley. SABATINA (8) is racing well, scoring second up at Narromine before sticking on well to place last time. Draws to get every chance.
